article:
This is a 'list of the 100 busiest airports in [[Europe]]', ranked by total
passengers per year, including both terminal and transit passengers. Data is for
2012 from provisional sources.

Lists of the rankings for 2011 and 2010 are also presented.

The tables also show the percentage change in total passengers for each
airport over the last year. Data is sourced individually for each airport and
normally originates from national aviation authority statistics, or those of
the airport operator.

European airports are defined as those that are within the airspace of the
member and candidate states of The Council of Europe.
